Name: Bench Press
Description: A weight training exercise where you lie on a bench and press a weight upwards.

Name: Push-Up
Description: An upper body exercise performed by lowering and raising the body using the arms.

Name: Pull-Up
Description: An upper body exercise where you pull yourself up until your chin is above the bar.

Name: Deadlift
Description: A weight training exercise where you lift a loaded barbell off the ground to the level of the hips.

Name: Bicep Curl
Description: An exercise that targets the biceps by lifting a weight with the elbow bending.

Name: Tricep Dip
Description: An exercise that targets the triceps by lowering and raising the body on parallel bars.

Name: Shoulder Press
Description: An exercise where you press a weight above your head.

Name: Lateral Raise
Description: An exercise where you raise the arms to the sides until they are parallel to the floor.

Name: Squat
Description: A lower body exercise where you lower your hips from a standing position and then stand back up.

Name: Lunge
Description: A lower body exercise where you step forward with one leg and lower your hips until both knees are bent at about a 90-degree angle.
